definition.value: A hematopoietic multipotent progenitor cell is multipotent, but not capable of long-term self-renewal. These cells are characterized as lacking lineage cell surface markers and being CD34-positive in both mice and humans.
A progenitor cell of any hematopoietic lineage, potentially multipotent.
A progenitor cell of any myeloid lineage, potentially multipotent.
A progenitor cell restricted to the myeloid lineage.

label.value: nasal and broncial associated lymphoid tissue macrophage
